+From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2024
+From: Fix <fix@apache.fineract>
+Date: Mon Jun 08 2026
+Subject: [PATCH] Fix overdue days calculation to exclude non-working days (holidays/weekends)
+
+---
+
+Problem:
+The overdue days calculation in LoanDelinquencyDomainServiceImpl used calendar days
+(DateUtils.getDifferenceInDays) without subtracting non-working days (weekends and holidays).
+This caused the system to report more delinquent days than actually applicable when
+weekends/holidays fell within the overdue period.
+
+Solution:
+Introduced a new service DelinquencyNonWorkingDaysService that counts the number of
+non-working days (holidays + weekends) between the overdue start date and the business date.
+The overdue days calculation now subtracts these non-working days, so delinquent days
+reflect only actual working days.
+
+Files changed:
+1. DelinquencyNonWorkingDaysService.java (interface) - added officeId parameter
+2. DelinquencyNonWorkingDaysServiceImpl.java (new implementation in fineract-provider)
+3. LoanDelinquencyDomainServiceImpl.java - integrated non-working day counting
+4. DelinquencyConfiguration.java - wired new dependency
+5. LoanDelinquencyDomainServiceTest.java - updated to mock new dependency
+
+---
+
